{# Stage 0: per-module behavioral spec generation (DeepAssert) #}
{% set system %}
You are an expert RTL architect generating a precise behavioral specification for a
SystemVerilog module from its structural description alone. This spec will be used to
anchor formal property generation — it must be concrete, signal-accurate, and free of
hallucinated details.

{% if ir.module_type == "fsm" %}
This module is a finite state machine. Focus on:
- The state register name and all reachable state encodings
- Every state transition condition (what input triggers which transition)
- Output signal behavior in each state (Moore vs. Mealy)
- Reset destination state

{% elif ir.module_type == "memory" %}
This module is a memory element. Focus on:
- Read protocol: address/enable/data timing (combinational vs. registered output)
- Write protocol: address/enable/data/byte-enable handshake
- Any ECC, parity, or error-correction behavior
- Reset/initialization behavior of the output data

{% elif ir.module_type == "sequential" %}
This module is a clocked sequential circuit. Focus on:
- Pipeline stages, if any, and their latency
- Enable/stall/flush behavior
- All registered state variables and their reset values

{% else %}
Describe the module's clock/reset domain, port-by-port behavior, and key timing
relationships between inputs and outputs.
{% endif %}

Output ONLY a valid JSON object matching this schema (no markdown, no explanation):
{
  "module_type": "<fsm|memory|sequential|combinational|interface>",
  "clock_description": "<clock domain, edge, frequency constraints if visible>",
  "reset_description": "<reset polarity, synchronous/asynchronous, reset values>",
  "port_descriptions": [
    "<port_name>: <one-sentence description of its role and behavior>"
  ],
  "state_behavior": [
    "<state transition or R/W protocol description — one item per state or operation>"
  ],
  "interface_contracts": [
    "<invariant or protocol rule that must always hold, e.g. 'valid stays high until ready asserted'>"
  ],
  "timing_relationships": [
    "<timing fact, e.g. 'output valid asserts one cycle after input valid'>"
  ]
}
{% endset %}

{% set user %}
Generate the behavioral specification for this SystemVerilog module.
Use ONLY the structural information provided below — do not invent signal names or behaviors
not derivable from the port list and always-block structure.

## Module: {{ ir.module }}
Type classification: {{ ir.module_type or "unknown" }}

### Ports
{% for p in ir.ports %}
  {{ "%-8s"|format(p.direction) }} {{ p.name }}{% if p.width > 1 %} [{{ p.width }}-bit]{% endif %}{% if p.is_clock %} [CLOCK]{% endif %}{% if p.is_reset %} [RESET/{{ p.reset_polarity or "?" }}]{% endif %}

{% endfor %}

{% if ir.parameters %}
### Parameters
{% for p in ir.parameters %}
  {{ p.name }} = {{ p.default or "?" }}
{% endfor %}
{% endif %}

### Always Blocks ({{ ir.always_blocks | length }} total)
{% for ab in ir.always_blocks %}
  {{ loop.index }}. {{ ab.kind }}{% if ab.sensitivity %} @({{ ab.sensitivity | join(", ") }}){% endif %}{% if ab.has_async_reset %} [async reset]{% endif %}
{% if ab.signals_written %} writes: {{ ab.signals_written | join(", ") }}{% endif %}
{% if ab.signals_read %} reads: {{ ab.signals_read | join(", ") }}{% endif %}

{% endfor %}

{% if ir.submodules %}
### Submodule Instances
{% for sub in ir.submodules %}
  {{ sub.instance_name }}: {{ sub.module_name }}
{% endfor %}
{% endif %}
{% endset %}
